          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-05-09 20:35:35.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-05-10 00:48:10.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-3270 statahead: NOT free entry name with RPC in flight",
        "message": "LU-3270 statahead: NOT free entry name with RPC in flight\n\nThere was a race in the code where statahead thread would send a\nRPC and then exit without waiting for RPC to complete. On thread\nexit all the statahead entries (in spite of replied or not) will\nbe freed, including the entry name which is allocated inside the\nstatahead entry. On the other hand, the entry name is referenced\nby related statahead RPC, so accessing the entry name in the RPC\ncontext after the statahead entry freed is invalid.\n\nTo avoid that, the new mechanism will allocate entry name in the\n'minfo' which is referenced by the statahead RPC and will NOT be\nfreed when the statahead entry is freed before the statahead RPC\nreplied. The RPC callback handler can free the orphan entry name\ntogether with the 'minfo'. On the other hand, If there is no RPC\nsent for the statahead entry (not necessary), then allocate/free\nthe entry name together with the statahead entry.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iec3a011f44b8ede8d6a133a07edf023008a3145e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
